pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: THE PRIZE IS SET BEFORE US.
The prize is set before us-
But children of the heav'nly King,
To win, our Lord implores us!
But children of the heav'nly King,
The eye of God is o'er us,
From on high, from on high!
He is nigh, He is nigh.
Before we reach the heaven'ly fields,
CH0.-By and by we shall meet Him,
Before we reach the heaven'ly fields,
By and by we shall greet Him,
And with Jesus reign in glory,
By and by, by and by;
By and by we shall meet Him,
By and by we shall greet Him,
And with Jesus reign in glory,
We yield to Him who pleadeth
From on high, from on high!
For naught from Him can sever;
And faith shall fail us never-
There's a Stranger at the door;
He is nigh, He is nigh.
Our home is bright above us;
He has been there oft before;
No trials there to move us,
But Christ our Lord to love us,
Let Him in ere He is gone;
Dwells on high: dwells on high!
Let Him in, The Holy One,
Open now to Him your heart;
If you wait He will depart;
Let Him in; He is your Friend;
And your soul He will defend,
He will keep you to the end;
E'en though it be a cross
Still all my song shall be,
Hear you now His loving voice;
Now, oh now, make Him your choice;
He is standing at the door,
Joy to you He will restore,
And His name you will adore;
Yet in my dreams I'd be
He will make for you a feast;
He will speak your sins forgin'n,
And when earth-ties all are riv'n,
He will take you home to heav'n.
All hail the power of Jesus' name!
Still all my song shall be,
And crown Him Lord of all.
Ye chosen seed of Israel's race,
Hail Him who saves you by His grace,
Come we that love the Lord,
And crown Him Lord of all.
And let our joys be known,
Join in a song with sweet accord,
Sinners, whose love can ne'er forget
Join in a song with sweet accord,
Go, spread your trophies at His feet,
And crown Him Lord of all.
And crown Him Lord of all.
